description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shropshire Community Health NHS Trust provide high quality, innovative health services in and near people’s homes. Our Registered General Nurses work with partners to ensure that our patients receive co-ordinated, effective care in their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join our bank staff?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With COVID-19 playing a big part in all of our lives, we are expanding our community nursing capacity over the winter period and need your support to ensure our patients get the excellent care that they deserve. The best part? This can be done around your commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working as bank staff provides flexibility;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift patterns – we offer a variety of shift patterns, from long days to traditional 7.5 hours on weekends and weekdays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations&lt;/strong&gt; – we operate from 6 localities so you can choose the area that works best for you;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oswestry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Market Drayton / Whitchurch&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shrewsbury&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telford&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bridgnorth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ludlow / Bishops Castle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with the flexibility of working around your commitments, by being out in the community, you can deliver care to patients in their own homes. This includes a wide range of activities that you can do in a focused, one-to-one basis with your patients. Not only will you be able to use the skills and experiences you have already gained, you can also pick up new learning along the way by seeing each case to conclusion. This can include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Complex holistic assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Admission avoidance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Palliative end of life care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medication administration – transdermal, IV, injections, rectal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LTC Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wound care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pressure ulcer care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nutrition assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Symptom management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continence care – catheterisation, bowel care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emotional support / advanced communication with Nursing care needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Self-care, empowerment and education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multidisciplinary working – you can work with various other community teams and expand your network as well as your knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine you’re the patient. That is the simplest way to explain our approach to healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care and compassion is at the heart of everything we do. We place the individual at the centre by listening to what they have to say, recognising their needs and responding appropriately. We want our patients to recognise that they are more than just their conditions and their treatments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a forward-looking trust, we’re committed to continuous improvement and we want you to share your ideas with us. We value everyone’s opinion in order to improve our services for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a RGN and this sounds like the kind of role and organisation that you want to be a part of, don’t hesitate to get in touch with us for more information. We want to make sure you are making the best decision for you and are happy to discuss career options with anyone who is thinking of pursuing a career with us.&lt;/p&gt;
